About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2" is the sixth film of the YRF Spy Universe franchise and will release on 14 August 2025. The film stars two of the greatest cinematic icons Hrithik Roshan and NTR, with Kiara Advani in the lead and is directed by Ayan Mukerji. ‚ÄúAlpha‚Äù, the seventh instalment in the franchise and Hindi cinema's first female-led YRF Spy Universe film, starring Alia Bhatt and Sharvari, is set to release on 25 December 2025.

snippet.title: COOLIE Trailer Reaction! With Vivan & Brandon | Rajinikanth | Nagarjuna Akkineni | Aamir Khan
snippet.description:
Vivan and Brandon react to the explosive trailer for Coolie, marking the fiery return of Rajinikanth in a mass-loaded, emotional action drama.

Directed by Lokesh Kanagaraj (Leo, Vikram), Coolie brings back Rajinikanth (Jailer, Kaala) in a powerful new avatar‚Äîmixing grit, style, and legacy. With Anirudh Ravichander‚Äôs pulse-pounding score and stunning visuals, the film promises high-octane action and deep-rooted emotion.

Vivan and Brandon break down the intensity, vintage Rajini swag, and Lokesh‚Äôs signature world-building. Coolie looks like a full-blown cinematic celebration of one of India‚Äôs biggest icons.

snippet.description:
Saiyaara (1980) Ft. Kishore Kumar full song (Old version) Old is Gold with a New Voice!

The full version is finally here! We converted the vocals sung amazingly by RJ Kisna into kishore da's voice using AI, and I produced the retro background music, let me know if ya'll want a breakdown of how I do these retro versions! 




üåç Follow me here for more fun and behind the scenes:
Instagram - 
@anshuman.sharma1 |   / anshuman.sharma1  
Twitter - @anshumonsharma |   / anshumonsharma  
Facebook - @anshuman.sharma111 |   / anshuman.sharma1  

Saiyaara (1980) ‚Äì Kishore Kumar's Saiyaara Full Song 
Step back in time and relive the golden era of Bollywood with Kishore Kumar's rare gem "Saiyaara" (1980). This soulful melody captures the essence of vintage romance, timeless lyrics, and the golden voice of Kishore Da that still resonates in every heart.

Whether you're a lifelong Kishore fan or discovering his magic for the first time, this song is a journey into the past that you don't want to mi

Credit goes to _Rakesh Sutradhar üôè

[Verse 1]
Tu paas hai mere paas hai aise
Mera koi ehsaas hai jaise

Tu paas hai mere paas hai aise
Mera koi ehsaas hai jaise

Haaye main mar hi jaaun
Jo tujhko na paaun
Baaton mein teri main raatein bitaaun

Honthon pe lamha lamha
Hai naam tera haaye
Tujhko hi gaaun main, tujhko pukaaroon

[Chorus]
Saiyaara tu toh badla nahin hai
Mausam zara sa rootha hua hai

Saiyaara tu toh badla nahin hai
Mausam zara sa rootha hua hai

[Verse 2]
Beetey lamhon se duniya basa loon
Main toh tere aansuon ka bana hoon

Meri hansi mein teri sadaayein
Teri kahaani khud ko sunaaun

Yaadon ke taare, yaadon ke taare tootenge kaise
Mere hain jo woh roothenge kaise

Beetey dinon ki kholi kitaabein
Guzre palon ko kaise bhula dein

Haaye main mar hi jaaun
Jo tujhko na paaun
Baaton mein teri main raatein bitaaun

Honthon pe lamha lamha
Hai naam tera haaye
Tujhko hi gaaun main, tujhko pukaaroon

[Chorus Repeat]
Saiyaara tu toh badla nahin hai
Mausam zara sa rootha hua hai

Saiyaara tu toh badla nahin hai
Mausam zara sa rootha hua hai

[Bridge]
Jis roz hum tum phir se milenge
Yeh saari baatein tujhse kahenge

Duniya mein chaahe ban jaayein jo bhi
Tere bina tab kuch na rahenge

[Outro]
Haaye main mar hi jaaun
Jo tujhko na paaun
Jo tujhko na paaun
Main mar hi jaaun

Honthon pe lamha lamha
Hai naam tera haaye
Tujhko hi gaaun main, tujhko pukaaroon

snippet.title: One Punch Man Season 3 - Official Trailer (English Subtitles)
snippet.description:
"One-Punch Man‚Äù returns with Season 3! Check out the latest trailer for the continuation of this series!

Saitama is a hero who only became a hero for fun. After three years of ‚Äúspecial training,‚Äù he‚Äôs become so strong that he‚Äôs practically invincible. In fact, he‚Äôs too strong‚Äîeven his mightiest opponents are taken out with a single punch. Alongside Genos, his faithful disciple, Saitama performs his official hero duties as a member of the Hero Association. One day, monsters claiming to be from the Monster Association suddenly appeared, taking a child of Hero Association executive hostage. snippet.description:
Panchaanana Films productions in association with PRK Audio
presents
Rippan Swaamy - A rural thriller set in the fictional Malnad village of Snana Kopa. The story unfolds after the mysterious suicide of Rippan Swaamy, leading to a trail of secrets, drama, and suspense. As the mystery deepens, the truth behind his name and death slowly unravels.

The film is set to release in theatres on August 29.
Listen to the audio exclusively on PRK Audio. üéµ

snippet.title: HIM | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
What would you sacrifice to become the greatest of all time?

From Oscar¬Æ winner Jordan Peele and Monkeypaw Productions, producers of the landmark horror films Get Out, Us, Candyman and Nope, comes a chilling journey into the inner sanctum of fame, idolatry and the pursuit of excellence at any cost, featuring an electrifying dramatic performance from Marlon Wayans (Air, Respect).

Former college wide-receiver Tyriq Withers (Atlanta, the upcoming I Know What You Did Last Summer) plays Cameron Cade, a rising-star quarterback who has devoted his life, and identity, to football. On the eve of professional football‚Äôs annual scouting Combine, Cam is attacked by an unhinged fan and suffers a potentially career-ending brain trauma.

Just when all seems lost, Cam receives a lifeline when his hero, Isaiah White (Marlon Wayans), a legendary eight-time Championship quarterback and cultural megastar, offers to train Cam at Isaiah‚Äôs isolated compound that he shares with his celebrity influencer wife, Elsie White (Julia Fox; Uncut Gems, No Sudden Move). But as Cam‚Äôs training accelerates, Isaiah‚Äôs charisma begins to curdle into something darker, sending his prot√©g√© down a disorienting rabbit hole that may cost him more than he ever bargained for.

The film features a dynamic supporting cast including alternative comedy legend Tim Heidecker (First Time Female Director, Us) and Australian comic Jim Jefferies (The Jim Jefferies Show), plus MMA heavyweight fighter Maurice Greene and hip hop phenoms Guapdad 4000 and Grammy nominee Tierra Whack, all three in their feature film debuts.

HIM is directed by Justin Tipping (Kicks) from an acclaimed Black List screenplay by Zack Akers & Skip Bronkie (creators of the sci-fi crime series Limetown) and by Justin Tipping. The film is produced by Ian Cooper (Nope, Us), Jordan Peele (Candyman, BlacKkKlansman), Win Rosenfeld (Candyman, Lovecraft Country) and Jamal M. Watson (Hala, Sprinter) for Monkeypaw Productions and is executive produced by David Kern and Monkeypaw‚Äôs Kate Oh.

snippet.title: OM - Brodha V [Official Music Video]
snippet.description:
#OM #BrodhaV #ConsciousRap #GayatriMantra #IndianHipHop

Spotify: https://tinyurl.com/4sw84n6b
Apple Music: https://tinyurl.com/adfmtjmp
Amazon Music: https://tinyurl.com/mvjzr97j

Song Credits: 

Song Name - OM
Music Produced by Brodha V 
Lyrics - Brodha V 
Mixed and Mastered by Vivek Thomas at VTP Studios 
Mix Assisted by Sibin Wilson 
Recorded by Akash Shivakumar at Audiokraft Studio
Shloka Singers: Dr. Samrath Manjunath, Roshan Gopinath, 
Sharath Chandra

Video Credits 

Director/DOP: Sujish Das       
Producer: Vighnesh Shivanand
Edit: Sujish Das  
DI & VFX: Jakes B Richard 
Production Studio: Imagine Buddha
Asso. Director: Jakes B Richard 
Asst. Director: Mathews J Pothoor, Bharath Rajan 
VFX Associate: Mathews J Pothoor
Artist PR & Management : Sana Shawkath Khan
Hair & Make Up: Anushruthi Saha
Styling: Daisy Reang

Publicity Stills: Rithvik 
BTS & On-Set Video - Royston Menezes 
Publicity design: Ashwin Ramesh

Additional Post Production Crew
Edit: Praveen, Lokesh Kandan, Melvin Fx: Vignesh Narayan, Sri Vfx
AI: Yuvanesh 
Roto: Charan
Music Marketing & Publicity: Sana Shawkath Khan

OM Lyrics: 

Verse 1 : 
A plate is a myth when the rent is due but hunger is home/
It hurts, straight in the ribs, when I suffer alone/
My stomach be yelling louder than my prayers at night/
My mind telling me to quit, I might take the advice/
Mama prayed for the light while I'm restraining the spark/
Pops worked through the dark but now I'm breaking his heart/
I sense the disappointment in the words they utter/
Teardrops that weigh tons come from hurting mothers/
Hate what I see in the mirror, I'm the cause for their shame/
Reflections of my failures, always calling my name/
Mental shackles are the only inheritance of the first born/
Heir to the trauma, so I carry the curse on/
Masking the emptiness, my smile is a prop/
Just like another lifeless attire that I rock/
My girl walked away, said rapping ain't a job, get a life/
I'd never make it, so I don't fit the plot of her life/
My inner fire is dying out, is why I'm losing my sleep/
Maybe I'll never get paid but Imma do this for me/
Like a candle in a storm, a script for doom/
Against fellas that always had silver spoons from within the womb/
My demos get passed around like an endless fable/
While nepotists be getting signed cuz they got friends in labels/
Rejection on the daily, believe me they crush/
The dreams of a kid, he wishes that he'd never wake up/
I hope the heavens will guide me in tryna move with conviction/
Before the darkness consumes me and I know I'm losing this mission/
I'll let the kid in me down, I see him fade away/
Like the sky, through the clouds on a rainy day/
One last look at those I need in my life/
One last look at those who believed I could fight/
And when I'm hopeless in this moment of quiet/
Wishing the story goes on, that's when it hit me like..../


Hook/ Crescendo: 

Om bhur bhuvaha svaha 
Tat savitur varenyam 
Bhargo devasya dhimahi 
Dhiyo yo nah prachodayat...

Verse 2: 

Grandma gone she said that you'd be the man/
To be the one to fulfill their wishes, their Genie's lamp/
Go be their hope, their beacon up high/
What are obstacles at the feet when you dream of the sky/
Curses and bad juju float along with toxins in air/
Keep curving them gold diggers like convex affairs/
You best believe that you the prospect of prayers/
So we climbed mountains 'fore we understood the concept of stairs/
Became one of the greatests, ascension assured/
Our pens went to war, swinging like a pendulum door/
See we was Bound to the trash and clowned for our bad luck/
But we hustled like a Gujju that's down to his last buck/
Found a niche in rap, the crowd appeal unmatched/
And we did it with more soul than South Korean maps/
Through this marathon we ran feuding with time/
Expending our passion, and influencing minds/
In these scars are scriptures of all that we overcame/
We show no pain, through poetry, give em that novocaine/
Our fans write to us about their stories of triumph/
On how their life and our music formed a holy alliance/
We ain't no stranger to sins, we caved in to the urges/
Corrupting our ways being a slave to our purpose/
Some problems can't be solved, cuz we're cracked at the core/
Like mathematics, it all starts where the brackets implore/
Wealth is a symbol, of a high that keeps our egos sedated/
Kid shoulda gave up, battling all the demons he made up/
But I'm glad you woke up, never doubted your imagined acclaim/
We needed you here for the sound of fans chanting your name/
So here's to one more look at those that need you in life/
And one more look at those that need you to fight/
And anytime you need a moment of quiet/
Just know that, the story goes on, let it hit you like..../

Hook/ Crescendo: 

Om bhur bhuvaha svaha 
Tat savitur varenyam 
Bhargo devasya dhimahi 
Dhiyo yo nah prachodayat...

OM Lyrics: 

Verse 1 : 
A plate is a myth when the rent is due but hunger is home/
It hurts, straight in the ribs, when I suffer alone/
My stomach be yelling louder than my prayers at night/
My mind telling me to quit, I might take the advice/
Mama prayed for the light while I'm restraining the spark/
Pops worked through the dark but now I'm breaking his heart/
I sense the disappointment in the words they utter/
Teardrops that weigh tons come from hurting mothers/
Hate what I see in the mirror, I'm the cause for their shame/
Reflections of my failures, always calling my name/
Mental shackles are the only inheritance of the first born/
Heir to the trauma, so I carry the curse on/
Masking the emptiness, my smile is a prop/
Just like another lifeless attire that I rock/
My girl walked away, said rapping ain't a job, get a life/
I'd never make it, so I don't fit the plot of her life/
My inner fire is dying out, is why I'm losing my sleep/
Maybe I'll never get paid but Imma do this for me/
Like a candle in a storm, a script for doom/
Against fellas that always had silver spoons from within the womb/
My demos get passed around like an endless fable/
While nepotists be getting signed cuz they got friends in labels/
Rejection on the daily, believe me they crush/
The dreams of a kid, he wishes that he'd never wake up/
I hope the heavens will guide me in tryna move with conviction/
Before the darkness consumes me and I know I'm losing this mission/
I'll let the kid in me down, I see him fade away/
Like the sky, through the clouds on a rainy day/
One last look at those I need in my life/
One last look at those who believed I could fight/
And when I'm hopeless in this moment of quiet/
Wishing the story goes on, that's when it hit me like..../


Hook/ Crescendo: 

Om bhur bhuvaha svaha 
Tat savitur varenyam 
Bhargo devasya dhimahi 
Dhiyo yo nah prachodayat...

Verse 2: 

Grandma gone she said that you'd be the man/
To be the one to fulfill their wishes, their Genie's lamp/
Go be their hope, their beacon up high/
What are obstacles at the feet when you dream of the sky/
Curses and bad juju float along with toxins in air/
Keep curving them gold diggers like convex affairs/
You best believe that you the prospect of prayers/
So we climbed mountains 'fore we understood the concept of stairs/
Became one of the greatests, ascension assured/
Our pens went to war, swinging like a pendulum door/
See we was Bound to the trash and clowned for our bad luck/
But we hustled like a Gujju that's down to his last buck/
Found a niche in rap, the crowd appeal unmatched/
And we did it with more soul than South Korean maps/
Through this marathon we ran feuding with time/
Expending our passion, and influencing minds/
In these scars are scriptures of all that we overcame/
We show no pain, through poetry, give em that novocaine/
Our fans write to us about their stories of triumph/
On how their life and our music formed a holy alliance/
We ain't no stranger to sins, we caved in to the urges/
Corrupting our ways being a slave to our purpose/
Some problems can't be solved, cuz we're cracked at the core/
Like mathematics, it all starts where the brackets implore/
Wealth is a symbol, of a high that keeps our egos sedated/
Kid shoulda gave up, battling all the demons he made up/
But I'm glad you woke up, never doubted your imagined acclaim/
We needed you here for the sound of fans chanting your name/
So here's to one more look at those that need you in life/
And one more look at those that need you to fight/
And anytime you need a moment of quiet/
Just know that, the story goes on, let it hit you like..../
